<br>
Now is the question of Ragefire pops. According to several sources after Nagafen and Magus Roykl are dead he will pop in 0 - 72 hours. After Zordak is killed he is supposed to be a 23-24 hour pop. I am not sure what a despawn is. All FG's need to be killed in the times in between.  So I think the guilds/people who need a cleric epic should set up Zordak reservations like this:<br>
<br>
Nagafen dead- Guild A gets to sit in that room for 0 - 72 hours waiting. After they kill Ragefire once they let the next guild know the time and tell their person to come have a seat and stare at the wall. If he pops in the first 20 minutes as with Aenae, great; the next guild comes on in after he is dead (or to help kill him  ). If he pops in hour 71, uhg what a long sit, but he dies and the next guild moves in. <br>
<br>
Then after the second Ragefire kiled the next guild moves in. They get the luxury of the 24 hour camp. <br>
<br>
Now we all know the Ragefire spawns are not set in stone, but I do believe that we will be very knowledgable of how he pops after the 15 clerics in waiting get through with him. I know this family of Luclin can work it out, and we will all be better off with more cleric epics.<br>
<br>
Also,  the cleric community begs of you, DO NOT attempt Ragefire if you cannot kill him.  He is not an easy kill, though easier than Telendor and gang, but still not a raid to take lightly.  Get prepared, get the right gear, and whip him right the first time.  He dies in under 1 minute if you do it right. Go over that and people start to get toasted.<br>
<br>
I am just trying to keep peace in our community.  Please post here and suggestions you have.  This is not a flame or rant thread, it is an attempt to work things out without anger or hurt feelings.  <br>
